{
  "texts": [
    "The time windows can be defined as either fixed or flexible, meaning that the start and end times of the activity can be adjusted within a certain range.",
    "The objective of this variant is to schedule the activities while taking into account the resource constraints such as limited availability of labour, equipment, and materials, in order to minimize the project duration while meeting the specified time window for each activity [3].",
    "Multi-skilled RCPSP (MS-RCPSP) is another variant of the RCPSP wherein each activity requires a set of skills to be performed [4].",
    "Each skill is associated with a different worker or resource (or possibly more than one), and each worker can have multiple skills (or alternatively machines/equipment are general purpose ones).",
    "The goal of this variant is to schedule the activities while taking into account the resource constraints such as limited availability of workers, equipment, and materials, in order to minimize the project duration."
  ]
}